    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but reporting it to the platforms won't do anything because they're part of the loop. it's like the system has already decided that the \"online me\" is the valid one and the \"physical me\" is just noise. i feel like i'm becoming a ghost in my own life because everything people recognize as \"me\" is happening in the cloud, not in reality. if an AI can predict my thoughts and thoughts so well that it acts for me before i even act, hasn't it basically replaced me? like, if the digital version is more \"active\" and \"real\" to the world than i am, what's left of the original?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
